="__p14">Multivariable analysis of daily number of contacts</p></div><div data-largeobj="" data-largeobj-link-rid="largeobj_idm139705321313088" class="xtable"><table frame="hsides" rules="groups" class="rendered small default_table"><thead><tr><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><strong>variable</strong></td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><strong>level</strong></td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><strong>coefficient</strong></td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><strong>95% Confidence Interval</strong></td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"><strong>p-value</strong></td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">constant</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">26.05</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">(16.76, 35.34)</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x0003c;0.001</td></tr><tr><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">sex</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">male</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">baseline</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">female</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">-1.44</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">(-5.30, 2.42)</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.466</td></tr><tr><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">accommodation</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Student halls</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">baseline</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1"></td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">other</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">-3.90</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">(-10.14, 2.34)</td><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1">0.228</td></tr><tr><td align="center" rowspan="1" colspan="1"># of people in househo